1. Usage Scenarios
Scenario 1: Purchasing a Specific Vinyl Record (Collector/Buyer)
User: Alex, a collector who knows they want a specific version of a rare vinyl album.
Goal: Find and purchase a vinyl record of a specific release version and in good condition for a fair price.
Steps:
Alex logs into their RecordShare account.

They use the Search bar to type in the album name and select the "MUSIC" category.
On the search results page, they use filters like the price range slider or genre categories to refine the results.

They view in-depth details of a filtered listing, checking the condition and release version of the product.

Satisfied with the condition and price, Alex clicks "Add to Cart".

Alex navigates to the cart (which shows "0 items - C$0.00" until updated) and clicks "Buy Item" (initiating the checkout process).

They confirm their contact and shipping information during checkout and proceed to Make Payment.

After payment, Alex checks the Track Orders page to view the updates on their purchase.
 
Scenario 2: Selling an Extra Copy of a Video Game (Seller)
User: Maya, a casual seller who wants to offload an extra copy of a video game they own.

Goal: List and track the sale of a physical video game.

Steps:
Maya logs into her RecordShare account.
She navigates to the "Sell Items" section and clicks "Add Products" (Create listings).

She fills out the listing form, including the product name, condition, price, and uploads photos of the physical game.

Maya clicks "Submit" to create the new listing.

Later, when the item sells, she receives a notification.

She navigates to "Track Orders" to view the order and update the delivery status once she has shipped the game.

She updates her account profile with her latest Products Sold count and a short Bio.

2. Hierarchical Task Analysis (HTA)
Goal: Purchase Physical Media
P0: Purchase Physical Media
1.  Find Item
1.1  Log in to RecordShare.
1.2  Search for item (by name or use filters).
1.3  Review search results.
1.4  View item details (condition, release version, price).
1.5  Add item to the Cart.
2.  Checkout & Pay
2.1  Access the Cart.
2.2  Review and edit cart items.
2.3  Select "Buy Item" / "Proceed To Payment".2.4 Enter/confirm shipping/contact information.
2.5 Make Payment.
3.  Follow Up
3.1  Track Order.
3.2  (Optional) Add Review for the purchased listing.
Plan 0:
Do 1.1 → 1.2 → 1.3 → 1.4. If satisfied with the item, do 1.5.
Then proceed to 2.1 → 2.2 → 2.3 → 2.4 → 2.5.
Finally, do 3.1 → 3.2 (optional).

